  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-ON-01 trigger)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict hemolysis indices for centrifugal blood pump configurations representative of ventricular assist device (VAD) duty points. A CFD-based hemolysis model of the FDA generic centrifugal pump was assessed under steady-state operating conditions at 6000 RPM and 5 L/min flow. Thirteen credibility factors were evaluated against ASME V&V 40-2018 requirements for a Model Risk Level 5 device context. Seven factors received formal assessment; six were flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across blood viscosity and pump speed distributions. Despite partial factor coverage, the overall credibility evidence package was reviewed and conditionally accepted by the assessment team pending supplementary validation data for the six unassessed factors. No structured Context of Use object is carried in this package; intended-use scope is conveyed only through this narrative.",
